"children":[
"Severe hyperthermia is temperature ≥40.0 °C (104.0 °F) resulting from a failure of normal thermoregulation. Findings include loss of consciousness, muscle rigidity, seizures, and rhabdomyolysis with kidney failure, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"disseminated intravascular coagulation",
"children":[
"DIC"
]
},
","
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute respiratory distress syndrome",
"children":[
"ARDS"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_s26_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"34921a",
"children":[
"Neuroleptic malignant syndrome may occur in patients who have abruptly discontinued ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"L"
]
},
"-dopa for Parkinson disease."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5664d4",
"children":[
"The serotonin syndrome is often caused by the use of ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor",
"children":[
"SSRI"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" and the addition of a second drug that increases serotonin release or blocks its uptake or metabolism."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
